 Brian  |title = The 17th Maine backstabbers, part 2|url =http://maineatwar.bangordailynews.com/2019/02/13/the-17th-maine-backstabbers-part-2/|publisher=Bangor Daily News|location=Bangor, ME|date=2019-02-13}}\n* U.S. War Department, [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/moa/browse.monographs/waro.html ''The War of the Rebellion'']: ''a Compilation of the [[Official Records of the American Civil War|Official Records]] of the Union and Confederate Armies''. Washington, DC: U.S. Government Printing Office, 1880&ndash;1901.\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|American Civil War}}\n* [[List of Maine Civil War units]]\n* [[Maine in the American Civil War]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20061229160318/http://www.state.me.us/sos/arc/archives/military/civilwar/3meinf.htm State of Maine Civil War Records Website]\n*[http://www.mainememory.net/bin/Detail?ln=4127 Photograph of the 17th Maine Infantry from the Maine Memory Network]\n\n[[Category:Maine Civil War regiments|17th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment]]\n[[Category:1862 establishments in Maine]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1862]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations disestablished in 1865]]\n\n\n{{AmericanCivilWar-unit-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hhfjbaker", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBibliography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/17th_Maine_Volunteer_Infantry"}
{"title_page": "Josh Rotham", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox AFL biography\n| name = Josh Rotham\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| nickname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|02|25|df =y}}\n| birth_place = \n| originalteam = [[West Perth Football Club|West Perth]]\n| draftpick  = No. 37 in the [[2016 AFL draft#2016 national draft|2016 national draft]]\n| debutdate = 6 April 2019\n| debutteam = {{AFL WCE}}\n| debutopponent = {{AFL Col}}\n| debutstadium = MCG\n| height =  193 cm\n| weight =  86 kg\n| position = \n| otheroccupation = \n| currentclub = {{AFL WCE}}\n| guernsey = 35\n| years1 = 2019-\n| club1 = {{AFL WCE}}\n| games_goals1 = 4 (0)\n}}\n\n'''Josh Rotham''' (born 25 February 1998) is an Australian rules footballer who plays for the [[West Coast Eagles]] in the [[Australian Football League]] (AFL). He was selected at pick #37 in the [[2016 AFL draft#2016 national draft|2016 national draft]].<ref>{{Citation | last = Beveridge | first = Riley | author-link = | date = 28 July 2018 | title = Eagles lock in promising young defender | periodical = AFL | url = https://www.afl.com.au/news/2018-07-28/eagles-lock-in-promising-young-defender }}</ref>  He made his senior debut against [[Collingwood Football Club|Collingwood]] in round 3 of the 2019 season.<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 30 May 2019 | title = West Coast Eagles lock away Josh Rotham and Harry Edwards on new deals | periodical = The West Australian | url = https://thewest.com.au/sport/west-coast-eagles/west-coast-eagles-lock-away-josh-rotham-and-harry-edwards-on-new-deals-ng-b881215725z  }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/J/Josh_Rotham.html Josh Rotham] from AFL Tables\n\n{{West Coast player squad}}\n{{2016 AFL national draft}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rotham, Josh}}\n[[Category:West Coast Eagles players]]\n[[Category:West Perth Football Club players]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian rules footballers from Western Australia]]\n[[Category:West Coast Eagles (WAFL) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox AFL biography\n| name = Josh Rotham\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| fullname = \n| nickname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|02|25|df =y}}\n| birth_place = \n| originalteam = [[West Perth Football Club|West Perth]]\n| draftpick  = No. 37 in the [[2016 AFL draft#2016 national draft|2016 national draft]]\n| debutdate = 6 April 2019\n| debutteam = {{AFL WCE}}\n| debutopponent = {{AFL Col}}\n| debutstadium = MCG\n| height =  193 cm\n| weight =  86 kg\n| position = \n| otheroccupation = \n| currentclub = {{AFL WCE}}\n| guernsey = 35\n| years1 = 2019-\n| club1 = {{AFL WCE}}\n| games_goals1 = 4 (0)\n}}\n\n'''Josh Rotham''' (born 25 February 1998) is an Australian rules footballer who plays for the [[West Coast Eagles]] in the [[Australian Football League]] (AFL). He was selected at pick #37 in the [[2016 AFL draft#2016 national draft|2016 national draft]].<ref>{{Citation | last = Beveridge | first = Riley | author-link = | date = 28 July 2018 | title = Eagles lock in promising young defender | periodical = AFL | url = https://www.afl.com.au/news/2018-07-28/eagles-lock-in-promising-young-defender }}</ref>  He made his senior debut against [[Collingwood Football Club|Collingwood]] in round 3 of the 2019 season.<ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author-link = | date = 30 May 2019 | title = West Coast Eagles lock away Josh Rotham and Harry Edwards on new deals | periodical = The West Australian | url = https://thewest.com.au/sport/west-coast-eagles/west-coast-eagles-lock-away-josh-rotham-and-harry-edwards-on-new-deals-ng-b881215725z  }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/J/Josh_Rotham.html Josh Rotham] from AFL Tables\n\n{{West Coast player squad}}\n{{2016 AFL national draft}}\n\n[[Category:West Coast Eagles players]]\n[[Category:West Perth Football Club players]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian rules footballers from Western Australia]]\n[[Category:West Coast Eagles (WAFL) players]]\n", "name_user": "DB1729", "label": "safe", "comment": "default sort", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josh_Rotham"}
{"title_page": "Born Slippy", "text_new": "<!-- Please confirm it is this version and not Born Slippy .NUXX before adding anything. If it is the version from Trainspotting, it is not this version -->\n{{distinguish||text=[[Born Slippy .NUXX]], another single by Underworld}}\n{{for|the song by [[Albert Hammond, Jr.]] called \"Born Slippy\"|Momentary Masters}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name        = Born Slippy\n| cover       = underworld_bornSlippy.jpg\n| alt         =\n| type        = single\n| artist      = [[Underworld (band)|Underworld]]\n| album       =\n| B-side      = \"[[Born Slippy .NUXX]]\", \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\"\n| released    = 1 January 1995\n| format      = [[12-inch single|12\" vinyl]], [[Compact Disc|CD]]\n| recorded    =\n| studio      =\n| venue       =\n| genre       = [[Techno]], [[hard trance]]\n| length      = 8:29\n| label       = [[Junior Boy's Own]], [[Wax Trax! Records]]\n| writer      = [[Rick Smith (musician)|Rick Smith]], [[Karl Hyde]], [[Darren Emerson]]\n| producer    = Rick Smith, Karl Hyde, Darren Emerson\n| prev_title  = [[Dirty Epic]]\n| prev_title2 = [[Cowgirl]]\n| prev_year   = 1994\n| next_title  = [[Rowla]]\n| next_year   = 1996\n}}\n\"'''Born Slippy'''\" is a single by British electronic group [[Underworld (band)|Underworld]]. It was released in January 1995 as a single, and has never appeared on an album by the group, although it was added as \"Born Slippy (original instrumental version)\" to the ''Super Deluxe'' reissue in 2015 of Underworld's album of March 1996, ''[[Second Toughest in the Infants]]''. The track is [[instrumental]], and features no lyrics. \n\nIt is separate to its B side \"[[Born Slippy .NUXX]]\", which appeared on the soundtrack to the film ''[[Trainspotting (film)|Trainspotting]]''. The single peaked on the [[UK Singles Chart]] during 1995 at #52.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_U.HTM |title=Chart Log UK |website=zobbel.de |accessdate=2008-06-21}}</ref> The song title comes from the name of a [[greyhound]], which the band had bet on and won.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2006/feb/24/popandrock2 | title=Twelve artists talk about making one of their classic tracks | publisher=The Guardian | date=2006-02-24 | location=London | first1=Dave | last1=Simpson | first2=Dorian | last2=Lynskey}}</ref> The \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" version remains exclusive to this single.\n\n== Track listing ==\n\n===Junior Boy's Own (United Kingdom)===\n==== 12\": JBO 29 ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n\n====12\": JBO 29R / JBO 29R Promo====\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n# \"Cowgirl (Winjer Mix)\" \u2013 6:25\n\n==== 2x12\": JBO 29 Promo ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n# \"Cowgirl (Winjer Mix)\" \u2013 6:25\n\n==== CD: JBO 29 CDS ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n\n===WaxTrax! TVT (United States)===\n==== 12\": TVT 8731-0 / CD: TVT 8731-2 ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n\n==Other remixes/versions==\n*2007 \u2013 Joe K \u2013 Born Slippy (Extended Club Mix)\n*2008 \u2013 Joe K \u2013 Born Slippy (Joe K vs. Beto Dias Remix)\n*2008 \u2013 Manuel De La Mare \u2013 Born Slippy (MDLM Mix)\n*2009 \u2013 Dankann \u2013 Born Slippy (David Jones Original Edit)\n*2017 \u2013 Underworld \u2013 Born Slippy (Jorn van Deynhoven Rework)\n*2018 \u2013 Andrew Meller \u2013 Born Slippy (Reincarnation Mix)\n\n== Notes ==\n* \"Born Slippy\" is sometimes given the label ''(original)'' or ''(instrumental)'' to distinguish it from \"Born Slippy .NUXX\", which features vocals by [[Karl Hyde]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.underworldlive.com Underworldlive.com]\n* {{MetroLyrics song|underworld|born-slippy}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Underworld}}\n\n[[Category:Underworld (band) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Darren Emerson]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Rick Smith (Underworld)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Karl Hyde]]\n[[Category:1995 singles]]\n[[Category:1995 songs]]\n[[Category:Wax Trax! Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please confirm it is this version and not Born Slippy .NUXX before adding anything. If it is the version from Trainspotting, it is not this version -->\n{{distinguish||text=[[Born Slippy .NUXX]], another single by Underworld}}\n{{for|the song by [[Albert Hammond, Jr.]] called \"Born Slippy\"|Momentary Masters}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name        = Born Slippy\n| cover       = underworld_bornSlippy.jpg\n| alt         =\n| type        = single\n| artist      = [[Underworld (band)|Underworld]]\n| album       =\n| B-side      = \"[[Born Slippy .NUXX]]\", \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\"\n| released    = 1 January 1995\n| format      = [[12-inch single|12\" vinyl]], [[Compact Disc|CD]]\n| recorded    =\n| studio      =\n| venue       =\n| genre       = [[Techno]], [[hard trance]]\n| length      = 8:29\n| label       = [[Junior Boy's Own]], [[Wax Trax! Records]]\n| writer      = [[Rick Smith (musician)|Rick Smith]], [[Karl Hyde]], [[Darren Emerson]]\n| producer    = Rick Smith, Karl Hyde, Darren Emerson\n| prev_title  = [[Dirty Epic]]\n| prev_title2 = [[Cowgirl]]\n| prev_year   = 1994\n| next_title  = [[Rowla]]\n| next_year   = 1996\n}}\n\"'''Born Slippy'''\" is a single by British electronic group [[Underworld (band)|Underworld]]. It was released in January 1995 as a single, and has never appeared on an album by the group, although it was added as \"Born Slippy (original instrumental version)\" to the ''Super Deluxe'' reissue in 2015 of Underworld's album of March 1996, ''[[Second Toughest in the Infants]]''. The track is [[instrumental]], and features no lyrics. \n\nIt is separate to its B side \"[[Born Slippy .NUXX]]\", which appeared on the soundtrack to the film ''[[Trainspotting (film)|Trainspotting]]''. The single peaked on the [[UK Singles Chart]] during 1995 at #52.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/CLUK_U.HTM |title=Chart Log UK |website=zobbel.de |accessdate=2008-06-21}}</ref> The song title comes from the name of a [[greyhound]], which the band had bet on and won.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2006/feb/24/popandrock2 | title=Twelve artists talk about making one of their classic tracks | publisher=The Guardian | date=2006-02-24 | location=London | first1=Dave | last1=Simpson | first2=Dorian | last2=Lynskey}}</ref> The \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" version remains exclusive to this single.\n\n== Track listing ==\n\n===Junior Boy's Own (United Kingdom)===\n==== 12\": JBO 29 ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n\n====12\": JBO 29R / JBO 29R Promo====\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n# \"Cowgirl (Winjer Mix)\" \u2013 6:25\n\n==== 2x12\": JBO 29 Promo ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n# \"Cowgirl (Winjer Mix)\" \u2013 6:25\n\n==== CD: JBO 29 CDS ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n\n===WaxTrax! TVT (United States)===\n==== 12\": TVT 8731-0 / CD: TVT 8731-2 ====\n# \"Born Slippy\" \u2013 8:29\n# \"Born Slippy .NUXX\" \u2013 9:44\n# \"Born Slippy .TEL EMATIC\" \u2013 9:39\n\n==Other Remixes/Versions==\n*2007 \u2013 Joe K \u2013 Born Slippy (Extended Club Mix)\n*2008 \u2013 Joe K \u2013 Born Slippy (Joe K vs. Beto Dias Remix)\n*2008 \u2013 Manuel De La Mare \u2013 Born Slippy (MDLM Mix)\n*2009 \u2013 Dankann \u2013 Born Slippy (David Jones Original Edit)\n*2017 \u2013 Underworld \u2013 Born Slippy (Jorn van Deynhoven Rework)\n*2018 \u2013 Andrew Meller \u2013 Born Slippy (Reincarnation Mix)\n\n== Notes ==\n* \"Born Slippy\" is sometimes given the label ''(original)'' or ''(