zarevich]] 7\n}}\n\n==Awards==\n{{winners|bk|1994 FIBA World Championship Winner|United States|Third}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center; margin:auto\"\n![[FIBA World Cup MVP|MVP]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Shaquille O'Neal]]\n|}\n\n===All-Tournament Team===\n{{main|FIBA Basketball World Cup All-Tournament Team}}\n*{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Sergei Bazarevich]]\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Reggie Miller]]\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Shawn Kemp]]\n*{{flagicon|Croatia}} [[Dino Ra\u0111a]]\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Shaquille O'Neal]] \u2014 [[FIBA World Cup MVP|MVP]] \nSource:<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://archive.usab.com/mens/national/10_mwc_feature_1994.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725020406/http://archive.usab.com/mens/national/10_mwc_feature_1994.html |archive-date=2015-07-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Top scorers (ppg)==\n\n# {{flagicon|Australia}} [[Andrew Gaze]] 23.9\n# {{flagicon|Croatia}} [[Dino Ra\u0111a]] 22.4\n# {{flagicon|Croatia}} [[Arijan Komazec]] 19.4\n# {{flagicon|South Korea}} [[Hur Jae]] 19.4\n# {{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Paolo de Almeida]] 19.4\n# {{flagicon|South Korea}} [[Moon Kyung-Eun]] 19\n# {{flagicon|Cuba}} [[Richard Matienzo]] 18.8\n# {{flagicon|USA}} [[Shaquille O'Neal]] 18\n# {{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Marcelo Nicola]] 17.7\n# {{flagicon|USA}} [[Reggie Miller]] 17.1\n\n==Final rankings==\n[[File:1994 FIBA World Championship final rankings.png|thumb|600px|1994 FIBA World Championship final rankings.]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n!width=200px|Team\n! Record\n|- bgcolor=gold\n! 1\n| {{bk|USA}}\n| 8\u20130\n|- bgcolor=silver\n! 2\n| {{bk|Russia}}\n| 6\u20132\n|-\n|- bgcolor=cc9966\n! 3\n| {{bk|Croatia}}\n| 7\u20131\n|-\n! 4\n| {{bk|Greece}}\n| 4\u20134\n|-\n|-\n! 5\n| {{bk|Australia}}\n| 5\u20133\n|-\n! 6\n| {{bk|Puerto Rico|1952}}\n| 3\u20135\n|-\n! 7\n| {{bk|Canada}}\n| 4\u20134\n|-\n! 8\n| {{bk|China}}\n| 2\u20136\n|-\n! 9\n| {{bk|Argentina}}\n| 5\u20133\n|-\n! 10\n| {{bk|Spain}}