 officials==\n\n*[[Calimesa, California|Calimesa]] City councilor Mayor and  Jeff Hewitt (2011-2015)(2015-2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsmirror.net/news/hewitt-voted-in-as-calimesa-s-new-mayor/article_efe8a2b2-9f73-11e5-827e-c71a30e5b349.html|title=Hewitt voted in as Calimesa's new mayor|website=NewsMirror.net|access-date=December 17, 2017}}</ref>\n*Bellflower city coucilor and mayor [[Art Olivier]] (1994-1997)(1998-1999)\n\n==Electoral performance==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Presidential nominee !! Votes !! Change\n|- \n| [[1972 United States presidential election in California|1972]] || [[John Hospers]] (write-in) || 980 (0.05%) || {{steady}}\n|- \n| [[1976 United States presidential election in California|1976]] || [[Roger MacBride]] || 56,388 (0.72) || {{increase}} 0.71%\n|-\n| [[1980 United States presidential election in California|1980]] || [[Ed Clark]] || 148,434 (1.73%) || {{increase}} 1.01%\n|-\n| [[1984 United States presidential election in California|1984]] || [[David Bergland]] || 49,951 (0.53%) || {{decrease}} 1.20%\n|-\n| [[1988 United States presidential election in California|1988]] || [[Ron Paul]] || 70,105 (0.71%) || {{increase}} 0.18%\n|-\n| [[1992 United States presidential election in California|1992]] || [[Andre Marrou]] || 48,139 (0.43%) || {{decrease}} 0.28%\n|-\n| [[1996 United States presidential election in California|1996]] || [[Harry Browne]] || 73,600 (0.73%) || {{increase}} 0.30%\n|-\n| [[2000 United States presidential election in California|2000]] || [[Harry Browne]] || 45,520 (0.42%) || {{decrease}} 0.31%\n|-\n| [[2004 United States presidential election in California|2004]] || [[Michael Badnarik]] || 50,165 (0.40%) || {{decrease}} 0.02%\n|-\n| [[2008 United States presidential election in California|2008]] || [[Bob Barr]] || 67,582 (0.50%) || {{increase}} 0.10%\n|-\n| [[2012 United States presidential election in California|2012]] || [[Gary Johnson]] || 143,221 (1.10%) || {{increase}} 0.60%\n|-\n| [[2016 U